A tiny, circular CD the size of a business card resting on a worn leather messenger bag, surrounded by scattered miniature tools and diagnostic equipment. The scene is rendered in warm, sun-faded colors with soft grain and rounded corners reminiscent of 1970s photography. A vintage desktop computer sits blurred in the background. The namecard CD catches golden afternoon light streaming through venetian blinds, casting delicate striped shadows across the composition. The mood evokes nostalgic frustration and the tactile joy of physical media from a simpler technological era.
